&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clean luxury. Better for you.&lt;/strong&gt; At Everlane, we believe luxury should be as effortless as it is conscious. We partner with ethical factories, work with premium, sustainably sourced materials, and strive to leave the industry cleaner than we found it. There&#39;s still much to do, and we&#39;re excited to grow a team of motivated humans ready for the challenge. The journey toward better continues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Everlane Creative team connects marketing and business objectives to the creative heartbeat of the brand. Made up of thinkers and makers, the team provides a vision and a framework for work that directly engages our customers, from product campaigns, to retail to e-commerce to social media and beyond. Key brand codes such as transparency, accessibility, and inclusivity inform our work and guide our unique culture.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an Associate Art Director to join the creative team to help bring the brand to life and evolve its design vision. Reporting into the Creative Director, you are responsible for concepting, designing, and delivering elevated creative solutions that support brand storytelling, seasonal campaigns, and commercial objectives. You will contribute to a wide range of projects with work spanning both the digital and physical space—anything from email and site design to in-store signage and paid advertising is fair game. You will work closely with the entire creative team to develop, concept and execute brand campaigns.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your day-to-day:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Creative Direction &amp;amp; Concept Development&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute compelling, on-brand creative concepts across integrated platforms including digital, social, print, and experiential.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Creative Leadership to translate brand vision into cohesive seasonal campaigns and storytelling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create mood boards, visual frameworks, and presentation decks to communicate creative direction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Actively contribute to brainstorming sessions and cross-functional ideation for campaigns and brand initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Design &amp;amp; Execution&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the design and production of assets across channels including social media, e-commerce, email, web, and marketing collateral.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the creation of homepage content, email layouts, and digital storytelling assets (video, interactive, and motion where applicable).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and develop visual assets for product launches, brand campaigns, and retail activations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support and execute print materials including lookbooks, mailers, packaging, and in-store/outdoor visuals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure consistency and excellence across all touchpoints, maintaining high standards of typography, layout, and brand identity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We&#39;d love to hear from you if you have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of experience within the field of design&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A strong portfolio showcasing work across a range of platforms: digital, print, paid, packaging and more&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working across e-commerce, social, and campaign-driven environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expert knowledge of typography, grid systems, color theory and composition. A background in motion graphics and illustration is a bonus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A passion for brand building and a strong understanding of how to maintain and evolve design systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced Creative Suite and Figma knowledge. AfterEffects proficiency is a bonus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience at an agency or high-end consumer brand preferred,

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clean luxury. Better for you.&lt;/strong&gt; At Everlane, we believe luxury should be as effortless as it is conscious. We partner with ethical factories, work with premium, sustainably sourced materials, and strive to leave the industry cleaner than we found it. There&#39;s still much to do, and we&#39;re excited to grow a team of motivated humans ready for the challenge. The journey toward better continues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Everlane Design team is a group of passionate people focused on creating product that lives up to our vision: Creating a sustainable way to build a forever wardrobe with a minimal impact on the planet. We believe there is no need to be any compromise between looking good, feeling good, and doing good. We are entrepreneurial and strategic in our approach. We are consumer-obsessed, data data-curious, and prioritize building product that is leading the way for the industry for sustainability and design.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All of the Design team champions the product across the company from Merchants, Marketing, Creative, Planning, Digital, and Product Development. Everyone on our team is accountable for our approach; to create an inclusive environment where diverse perspectives are encouraged and both past experiences and new ways of thinking are valued.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Color Design Associate supports the Design Managers and VP of Design in creating seasonal color palettes and visual assets, as well as in managing dip and basic pattern development and approvals. Reporting into the Design Manager, you will play a key role in shaping how our color and pattern are internally executed and externally experienced by our customers. Success in this role will be defined by a precise focus on maintaining bulk color consistency and ensuring pattern continuity and accuracy across the collection. The ideal candidate is a collaborative team player who values feedback as a tool for growth.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your day-to-day:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist the Design Managers in seasonal color palette creation, develop patterns, and execute through to bulk fabrications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build physical and digital color and pattern palettes led by seasonal concept boards (concept team owned)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build Product Playbook and other visual communication assets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assists in coloring the line: filling CAD pages and maintaining visual line sheets with the direction of Design Managers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Owns loading dip and artwork requests with the information of correct fabrication, dye technique, and print specifications shared by the Design Managers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build Pitch sheets for artwork/pattern development with guidance from Design Managers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for color approvals with support from Design Managers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organize &amp;amp; maintain dip approval binder, dip folders, and all digital tracking of dip approvals and color names&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Works closely with Raw Materials to understand color and pattern feasibility across all materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Design &amp;amp; Merchandising teams to understand color and pattern performance to inform future palette and pattern decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with cross-functional teams with Design Managers: Raw Materials, Sourcing, Product Development and Merchandising.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We&#39;d love to hear from you if you have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of experience in color design, color analyst, textile, concept or similar role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s Degree in Fashion or closely related design field&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Elevated eye for color and pattern with an innate sense of relevant brand trends&l

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clean luxury. Better for you.&lt;/strong&gt; At Everlane, we believe luxury should be as effortless as it is conscious. We partner with ethical factories, work with premium, sustainably sourced materials, and strive to leave the industry cleaner than we found it. There&#39;s still much to do, and we&#39;re excited to grow a team of motivated humans ready for the challenge. The journey toward better continues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Everlane is building a first-class design team, and we are currently looking to fill a Director who will focus on Women’s and Men’s Apparel. You must be passionate, enthusiastic, with an obsessive eye for detail along with an entrepreneurial spirit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting into the SVP of Design &amp;amp; Brand Creative, you will lead a team to create commercially successful, relevant and timeless apparel products. From product ideation to final pre-production prototypes, you will be responsible for the design sketches to the executions of your categories. You must also demonstrate leadership, use creative &amp;amp; analytical skills to set a short-term and long-term strategy for your function and your people with clear goals. To this end, you will work closely with your cross functional partners in Merchandising, Technical Design, Raw Materials, Sourcing, Production and your peers in Women’s and Men’s design.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your day-to-day:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Brainstorm new product concepts with SVP of Design at Seasonal Product Ideation, with Merchandising partners and cross- functional thought partners at Product Milestone.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Initiate product and fabric development to satisfy long term business needs within our Sustainability pipeline&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travel internationally and domestically for vendor direction, inspiration and fabric shows&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategically develop and grow the Women’s &amp;amp; Men’s business in line with company targets defined by our long-range plan&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and develop core knits, sweaters, wovens, and accessories on a quarterly basis with strategic mindset for platformed fabrications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and present quarterly sketch reviews, check-ins with SVP of Design along with pipeline milestone overlaps of seasons&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guide team to achieve an elevated fit direction (includes Italian workmanship)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor and lead direct reports&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In collaboration with Merchandising, TD &amp;amp; PD, manage calendar, budget and team activities from weekly touch bases to milestone engagement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We&#39;d love to hear from you if you have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have 10+ years experience designing Sweaters, Knits and Woven Apparel with Italian tailoring knowledge &amp;amp; ability to do simple draping.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have 4+ years experience managing and mentoring teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have 4+ years experience with private label accessories (footwear, handbags, soft items &amp;amp; collaborations)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of building and developing knit and sweater and woven businesses and have worked at scale&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep technical knowledge of knitted fabric, sweaters yarns and woven fabrics &amp;amp; Italian tailoring /vendors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High competency with fittings (concise, directive communication to lead a cross-functional fitting)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong P.O.V on relevant trend&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with co-creation, testing off-shore and near-shore process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
