&lt;p&gt;Everlane is looking for a highly motivated Director to join our Finance team and lead the FP&amp;amp;A function to support Everlane’s next phase of growth.&amp;nbsp; You will play a critical role in generating financial and operational insights that drive business results. You will serve as the finance partner to each of our business functions and influence decision-making consistent with our strategies and aligned to our financial goals.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate is highly analytical, strategic, detail-oriented, and curious. You thrive in a fast-paced environment and are able to multitask, prioritize projects and roll up your sleeves to get the job done. You have the capability and vision to scale the function in-line with company growth.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position reports directly to the CFO. This is a full-time virtual role, but we are partial to candidates in the Los Angeles area.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your day-to-day:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the monthly, quarterly and annual cycles for financial forecasting and reporting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the overall Company financial model (P&amp;amp;L, Balance Sheet, Cash Flow)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Innovate and improve the cross-functional financial planning processes, reporting standards and KPIs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide decision-support to business partners across the company on key financial and operational topics through data analysis and business understanding&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Go deep with ad hoc analysis to generate business insights and develop actionable recommendations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for Board &amp;amp; Parent Group updates and Financial Management Reporting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We&#39;d love to hear from you if you have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years of progressive experience and demonstrated growth in Finance/FP&amp;amp;A positions - ideally with roles in both large, well-run public companies and smaller, high-growth companies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in e-commerce, retail, apparel or consumer sectors is required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of&amp;nbsp; Customer Analytics and Digital Marketing is highly desirable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical capability and hands-on willingness to build complex financial models and conduct detailed data analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong interpersonal skills with demonstrated track-record for building collaborative relationships across all levels of the organization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
