&lt;p&gt;The Raw Materials team at Everlane researches, sources, and develops all materials used in the creation of Everlane products. We scour the globe for innovative and sustainable opportunities within materials, and look for curious and passionate individuals with an innate love of tactile product development to join our team. We partner closely with Design, Product Development, and Sourcing to develop best-in-class materials that can deliver on premium quality, cost, and sustainability.&amp;nbsp; Building lasting partnerships with our suppliers is of utmost importance, as we partner to lead the industry in transparency and sustainable sourcing. We dive deep into material origins and the path fibers take to finished goods, to understand social and environmental impacts from &#39;seed to fabric&#39;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a &lt;strong&gt;Senior Associate, Raw Materials – Knits &amp;amp; Trims&lt;/strong&gt; to play a critical role in supporting the development and execution of our knit materials strategy. You will contribute a strong point of view on fabric innovation, deep curiosity for fibers and construction, and a passion for sustainability. You will manage key aspects of seasonal development, supplier engagement, and material execution, while helping to evolve tools, processes, and standards across the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role reports to the Senior Manager of Raw Materials and serves as a key contributor to both the creative and operational success of the Raw Materials function.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your day-to-day:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead execution of knit material and trim development across seasons, from concept and sourcing through final adoption&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Design and Product Development on the development of knit fabric and trim assortments, balancing innovation, cost, and scalability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a key point of contact for all knit material and trim topics across cross-functional teams and suppliers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead knit fabric and trim development with suppliers, including briefing, sampling, testing, and iteration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate technical feasibility, performance, and risk, proactively problem-solving to meet product requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build strong partnerships across Design, Product Development, Merchandising, QA, and Sourcing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own accuracy and execution of material data within PLM and seasonal tools (WFX, MDD), ensuring data integrity across the product lifecycle&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and implement process improvements to streamline development workflows and enhance team efficiency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support Sr. Manager of Raw Materials with total-brand initiatives and deliverables including system/data management, color/pattern development &amp;amp; tracking, organization, and presentation boards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and evolve fabric libraries and archives as a strategic resource&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Schedule and lead all appointments with knit mills and trim vendors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
