&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Senior Merchant&lt;/strong&gt; to lead our Men’s Apparel and Shoes &amp;amp; Accessories (ShaCC) businesses. This role will have strategic accountability over these key divisions and will be responsible for the high-level growth and in-season management of the portfolios. This role will partner with executive leadership and cross-functional teams to define the strategic vision, build multi-category assortment architectures, and drive global business results. Our ideal candidate has extensive experience in Men’s apparel and/or footwear and accessories merchandising, with a proven track record of managing complex divisions and driving multi-year growth strategies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your day-to-day:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Architect long-term divisional product strategies for Men’s and ShaCC to maximize market share and profitability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead complex category and color assortments, global launch calendars, and strategic tiered pricing models&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage predictive analytics, Market place analytics and &amp;nbsp; AI-driven insights to proactively identify growth pockets and optimize in-season inventory, moving beyond reactive recapping to aggressive, data-backed commercial decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee Omni-channel assortment strategies, ensuring brand synergy across online and physical retail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive cross-functional alignment with Design, Production, and Marketing to execute seamless 360-degree product stories&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage existing processes, systems, and calendars and create new ones to drive efficiency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cultivate an agile, &#39;test-and-learn&#39; environment. Comfortable adjusting category strategies based on real-time performance indicators—particularly in high-growth segments—and pivot assortments quickly to capture emerging trends.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We&#39;d love to hear from you if you have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4+ years of progressive merchandising experience, preferably across apparel and accessories&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep knowledge of the Men’s apparel, Women&#39;s footwear, and&amp;nbsp; Women&#39;s accessories global marketplace&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A proven track record of managing a category with an entrepreneurial &#39;owner&#39;s mindset&#39;—you don&#39;t just manage categories; you relentlessly optimize them for profitable growth.&lt;/li&gt;
